        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 7 at 6:40PM EDT by NWS Gaylord MI</headline>
        <description>At 639 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Lachine, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lachine, Long Rapids, Hillman, Spratt, and Cathro.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
